<!-- 4.5.17 -->
<div class='toload corollary'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Corollary 4.5.17</span>
	Let $G$ be a group, $S=\mathbf{S}(G)$ and $\theta$ a topological partial action of $S$ on $X$. Then there exists a global action $\alpha$ of $S$ on $X$ such that $\theta_s\leq\alpha_s$ for all $s\in S$ and $S\ltimes_\theta X\cong S\ltimes_\alpha X$.
	</p>
</div>